spans.text: THrough every Age some Tyrant Passion reigns
THrough every Age some Tyrant Passion reigns
And proudly still aspires to be possessed Of Her
sure iT had turned his Brain
) Thanking the Fates , who thus his Loss supplied
A Staff it feels , nor shall my want of Eyes , Make me believe
through thy Malice be of this bereft
Distastes , t'allay thy envied Gains , Unthought of , on the parsimonious Plains
some convenient Day , To face the Sun
The merry Bagpipe , which , ere fall of Night , Could sympathising Birds to tuneful Notes invite
thee leave a Life so fondly prised , To be in Crouds , or envied , or despised
